ChildRules.RuleName: Filter leading and trailing spaces from ISA/GS fields

Attributes._Description: "Because there can be multiple NTEs on a single detail line there are problems with associating them with the detail line they belong to.  For instance, if you get 3 detail lines with an NTE on each one plus another on line 1 then the NTE_Segment_Line field will have 4 lines while the DOS only has 3 lines.  At that point you don't know which NTE goes with which line.\015\012\015\012To solve that we write line numbers to a field (LXLineNum) and the current line to a field tracking line numbers with NTEs (NTELXLineNum).  This done at EDI mapping time in the input driver.  With this UDF we step through each line and each NTELine and match up associations.  If we get more than one NTE on a line we merge them with \042; \042.  \015\012\015\012This UDF is not as efficient as it could be.  Given the possiblity of 10 NTEs per line this UDF has a potential to do 10*n^2 iterations."
"With the way the iteration works you will be left with one final value in the Temp_NTE field.  This will get that value plus move the values to the \042real\042 field."
